      <span style="font-weight:bold"> Bio: </span> She is the co-owner and executive chef of three award-winning Chicago restaurants,
      Girl and the Goat, and Little Goat, duck duck goat, and opened her first restaurant, Scylla (now closed) as chef-owner at the
      age of 27. Izard won a coveted James Beard Foundation Award (Best Chef: Great Lakes) in 2013 for her work at Girl and the Goat.
      Izard has made a number of appearances on Top Chef since her win, both as a guest judge and participant (on Top Chef Duels).
      Stephanie was the show's first female winner, and claimed a $100,000 prize. Over the course of the season, Izard won two
      "Quickfire" challenges, five elimination challenges, and was on the top eleven out of fourteen episodes. In the Puerto Rico-based
      finale, she chose Eric Ripert to assist with her prep work in preparing a four-course tasting menu for judging, which prevailed
      over the menus offered by fellow contestants Richard Blais and Lisa Fernandes.
